-- India cbank bars banks from charging prepayment fee on floating rate term loans
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury
-- Wed May 07, 2014 02:44AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 7 (Reuters) - The Reserve Bank of India has barred banks from levying foreclosure charges on individual borrowers for all floating rate loans with immediate effect, it said in a release on Wednesday.

